E.D.I.T.H. ("Even Dead, I'm The Hero")
======================================

E.D.I.T.H. is an ORIGINAL project — its own codebase. It is NOT a fork or clone of any
other agent. We studied two existing open-source agents as references and, where it
genuinely helped, reimplemented specific ideas with attribution.

References studied (both MIT-licensed):
  - Hermes Agent — Nous Research — https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent
    Learned from: self-improving skill loop, SQLite/FTS5 memory, sandbox backends,
    multi-provider LLM layer, Camoufox browser approach.
  - OpenClaw — OpenClaw Foundation — https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw
    Learned from: channel-adapter gateway pattern, Playwright/CDP browser stack.

The full reference repositories are kept locally only (gitignored under reference/) and
are never committed here. Any code adapted from either project carries an inline comment
naming the source and its MIT license.

ruflo (v3.10.x) is used only as a BUILD-TIME orchestration tool. It is NOT a runtime
dependency of E.D.I.T.H.
